Within the brain ECF, diffusion of molecules is reduced by the hindrance of obstacles, including cells (see “Drug transport within the brain fluids” in “Processes affecting drug distribution within the brain”). To take the complexity of the brain ECF into account, the diffusion equation should be modified by including the tortuosity (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
